Two people were killed and two others injured when a truck and light motor vehicle collided on the N3 Highway at the Applesden turn in Pietermaritzburg, KwaZulu-Natal. Upon arrival, paramedics found both the truck and light motor vehicle on the side of the road, at the bottom of an embankment. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said: “The light motor vehicle was found partially beneath the bed of the truck. Several trees had collapsed and fallen onto the truck.” Paramedics discovered that two men, one from each vehicle, had sustained numerous, fatal injuries. Sadly, they were declared dead on the scene. “Two other patients were found on the scene by paramedics. The patients were assessed and found with minor to moderate injuries.” The injured patients were transported to nearby hospitals for further care. -TNA Reporter